Have a gimmick - something novel - e.g breaking the physical safe
Sandbox examples, discover the vulnerability, use the exploit to gain access and then issue a fix - learn the whole lifecycle
Be wary of just doing elongated code reviews 
Try to ensure training delegates already have 10-20% of the knowledge or experience already so they can get the most form the session 
Red Team + Blue Team = Purple Team
Competent developers - who know their application - who can walk through the code will build their own security awareness
Should everyione do security training?  IS it fair on everyone?
Train developers to be inquisitive, what is underneath hwo do things join together, not just that the function calls work?
Can you decompose your application?
